The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 January is 171,489 (19,765.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 January, there were 7,584 new confirmed cases (874.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 January, there were 12,471 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 39% (4,887 fewer cases).
